org.ambraproject.wombat.service.remote

Class CachedRemoteService<S extends Closeable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ambraproject.wombat.service.remote.CachedRemoteService<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    RemoteService<S>

    public class CachedRemoteService<S extends Closeable>
extends Object
implements RemoteService<S>
    Decorator class that adds caching capability to a wrapped RemoteService object. The uncached RemoteService methods are still available through delegating methods.

      • getResponse

        public org.apache.http.client.methods.CloseableHttpResponse getResponse(URI targetUri,
                                                               org.apache.http.Header... headers)
                                                                 throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: RemoteService
        Makes a request to the given URI, checks for response codes 400 or above, and returns the response.

        The caller must either close the returned CloseableHttpResponse object or close the InputStream to the response body (i.e., CloseableHttpResponse.getEntity().getContent()). This is very important, because leaving responses hanging open can starve the connection pool and cause horrible timeouts.

        Specified by:
        getResponse in interface RemoteService<S extends Closeable>
        Parameters:
        targetUri - the URI to which to send the request
        headers - headers to add to the request, if any
        Returns:
        response from the server
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is an error connecting to the server

      • requestCached

        public <T> T requestCached(String cacheKey,
                  URI address,
                  CacheDeserializer<? super S,? extends T> callback)
                throws IOException
        Get a value either from the cache or by converting a stream from a REST request or from the cache.

        If there is a cached value, and the REST service does not indicate that the value has been modified since the value was inserted into the cache, return that value. Else, query the service for a new stream and convert that stream to a cacheable return value using the provided callback.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of value to deserialize and return
        Parameters:
        cacheKey - the cache key at which to retrieve and store the value
        address - the address at which to query the service if the value is not cached
        callback - how to deserialize a new value from the stream, to return and insert into the cache
        Returns:
        the value from the service or cache
        Throws:
        IOException
